  "course_aims": {
    "label": "Course Aims",
    "value": "The aim of this course is to provide an overview of intelligent agent design, where agents perceive their environment and act rationally to fulfil their goals.  Students will gain practical experience in labs, programming various aspects of intelligent systems."
  },
  "intended_learning_outcomes_of_course": {
    "label": "Intended Learning Outcomes of Course",
    "value": "By the end of the course students will be able to:\nDemonstrate familiarity with the history of AI, philosophical debates, and understand the potential and limitations of the subject in its current form;\nExplain the basic components of an intelligent agent, and be able to map these onto other advanced subjects such as information retrieval, computer vision, database systems, robotics, human-computer interaction, reactive systems etc\nDiscuss difficulties in computer perception;\nDiscuss basic issues in planning;\nExplain and apply search-based problem-solving techniques;\nFormulate and apply Bayesian networks in modelling and planning;\nExplain and apply utility theory as a probabilistic framework for rational decision making;\nExplain and apply basic machine learning techniques to learn from rewards and observations."
  },
